  "body": "For beacon chain design, a validator will deposit 32 ETH to the main chain smart contract. The deposits are done via a one way burn contract on the main chain. A validator can withdraw the deposit in later phase from the beacon chain to the shard.\r\n\r\nIn order to track validator registrations and deposits in shards, this issue explores the idea of develop the smart contract in Solidity. In summary, this smart contract consists of:\r\n\r\n- create the `deposit` function, which takes arguments `pubkey` in bytes, `withdrawal_shard_id` in int, `withdrawal_addr` in address and `randao_commitment` in bytes32\r\n- `deposit` emits a log with all params\r\n- `deposit` function should prevents multiple deposits of the same `pubkey`",
